  {
   "user": "Othmangba",
   "message": "I spent a whole month at Edge Esmeralda I'm going to write something but for now I will leave the log with all the lessons I learned and observations I had with no context behind them haha, if you're curious as to how I came to understanding that lesson or made that observation feel free to ask :). \n\n__Mid 2nd week reflections__\n- Tons of smart people\n- I've encountered some grifters, gotta get good at sorting through them\n- I have so much work to do\n- Need to 10x my communication skills, thought I was good\n- The answer to my technical problems is becoming more clear\n- Building out my metaphorical board of advisors\n- Be careful sharing your ideas and methodology\n\n__Week 3 reflections__\n\n- Bend or break, you choose\n- the larpers don't want it enough and get weeded out when things get hard\n- If you have a good idea ppl will try to steal it but it's not THAT good if people can steal it and deliver the same value\n- The ppl most threatened or made insecure by you will try to plant seeds of doubt\n- Set \"impossible\" goals for yourself under strict constraints and watch how creative your thinking gets\n- Less is more\n- The Social game just as important as the technical game, prolly even more",
   "timestamp": "2026-07-21T21:12:19.332000+00:00",
   "channel": "👀othmangba-log",
   "channel_id": "discord:1496590528865894672",
   "thread": null,
   "thread_id": null,
   "reply_to": null,
