  {
   "user": "Othmangba",
   "message": "__Week 4 reflections__\n\n- You can absolutely push multiple threads at once even if it seems overwhelming or impossible at first. This discomfort is where growth resides.\n- It's important to stay grounded in tangible results but don't let your level of progress dim the vision you would like to communicate. Tricky balance because you don't want to be seen as a grifter but also you don't want to appear unconfident. Epistemic humility while building a business is important but it doesn't sell.\n- You'll encounter more allies than enemies, the enemies may be frustrating but the fake allies are where time could be wasted. Don't worry about what people say but observe what they do and how they follow up on what they say.\n- Always have something to offer, give more than you take.\n- JOMO, joy of missing out. You don't have to do everything\n- Some people are interested in your story, some people are not. Don't take it personal.\n-  The same way you intentionally craft your information diet should be the same way you craft your community and support system.\n- Be honest about your capacity in lower priority commitments and apologize if you over extend. Have the decency to communicate this.\n- Don't be attached to your previous identity, you are meeting people where they are at during their life and they are meeting you where you are at. The most durable relationships will stand the test of time. If it's meant to be it's meant to be.",
   "timestamp": "2026-07-21T21:12:23.028000+00:00",
   "channel": "👀othmangba-log",
   "channel_id": "discord:1496590528865894672",
